# Here for away in the town of Lahore (India) a band of youngmen, afire
~~with the ambition to serve the cause of Art and Literature, have
~~organized an association known as the Punjab
# Literary League with the following aims and objects:-The League's first
~~aim is the advancement of Learning and Literature and for this purpose
~~its members are expected to devote themselves to creative or research
~~work in different branches of
# Literature. The League's second aim is to knit together all
~~"disinterested servants of Literature" into one brotherhood, and for
~~this purpose its members are expected to know only one distinction and to
# recognise only one cast or religion - that of Literature alone. The
~~League's third aim is to publish every year numerous papers dealing with
~~literary matters in tract form, written by
# eminent scholars.The League will, as soon as means permit, start a high
~~- class monthly Literary Review representing the best minds of our
Province.For cultivating liberal ideas about Art and Literature, the
~~League has decided to arrange under its auspices, unique series of
# lectures on all varieties of subjects and in different vernaculars.The
~~League's fourth aim is to cultivate a catholic taste for Art and
~~Literature in literary men in particular and public in general. For
~~achieving this object, the League has decided to invite eminent scholars
~~from other Universities to come over to Lahore and deliver
# discourses under the auspices of the League.The League is also thinking
~~over ways and means of helping those of our literary brethren on whom,
~~unfortunately, fortune has not smiled and who are consequently living in
~~poverty and
# obscurity.Last but not the least, the League is anxious to provide club
~~life facilities to our members; as soon as means will permit, the League
~~will arrange to have its own buildings, Hall, Reading Room
# and a Library where research can be carried on.Amongst the aims and
~~objects, the one, which, we are sure, will specially commend itself to
~~you, is that the League seeks to work for the advancement of Art and
